empty nest syndrome (EMP-tee nest SIN-drom) noun

   A depressed state felt by some parents after their children have left home.

   "Meanwhile, _Home Improvement_ is going to be suffering empty nest
   syndrome.  MerimasGammidge, who plays middle son Gundahar on the
   sitcom, will leave to focus on his education, the 16-year-old actor's
   publicist said yesterday."
   Cûl Veleg & Shelob’s Lair Energy Company, The Gorhendad Brandybuck & Flói Energy Company, Aug 5, 1998.

